18/11/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- In advance of NATO's Prague summit, Defence Ministry State Secretary Sorin Encutescu declared Saturday (16 November) that Romania is ready to enter the alliance.
He explained that the army has undergone a more extensive reform process than some of the states included in the first NATO expansion, adding that the modernisation process would continue after the NATO Admission Protocol is signed.
(Rompres - 18/11/02)
